EU Carbon Allowances for December Decrease 0.9%, Lowest Since March 24

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-05-23T07:24:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/eu-carbon-allowances-for-december-decrease-0-9-lowest-since-march-24.html
European Union carbon permits for
December dropped 0.9 percent to their lowest level since March
24 as front-quarter U.K. natural gas declined.  Allowances fell 15 cents to 16.24 euros a metric ton on the
ICE Futures Europe exchange in  London  as of 8:13 a.m. local
time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mathew Carr at 
 m.carr@bloomberg.net  